project_rules:
	•	id: cloakcat-project-overview
patterns:
	•	“**/*.rs”
	•	“**/*.toml”
languages:
	•	rust
rules:
	•	

This repository is “CloakCat C2”, a Rust-based Command and Control framework.
It consists of three main components:
	1.	cat-server: Axum + sqlx(PostgreSQL) based C2 HTTP API server.
	2.	cat-agent: Rust beacon/agent that executes shell commands received from the server and uploads results.
	3.	cat-cli: Operator CLI tool that lists agents, sends commands, and fetches results.
	•	

When modifying code, keep existing style and naming conventions.
Prefer minimal, focused changes instead of large refactors.
	•	

Do not introduce new dependencies unless they are strictly necessary for the requested change.
If a new dependency is required, explain why in a short comment in the code.
	•	

Prefer small, composable functions and clear data flow.
Keep public APIs (function signatures, public structs) stable unless explicitly asked to change them.
	•	

Assume PostgreSQL is used via sqlx.
When adding persistence, use sqlx query macros and existing database patterns in this repo.
	•	id: cloakcat-security-opsec
patterns:
	•	“cat-server/**/*.rs”
	•	“cat-agent/**/*.rs”
languages:
	•	rust
rules:
	•	

This is a security/red team research project.
Focus on robustness, clear error handling, and avoiding obvious security mistakes.
	•	

Keep secrets (keys, tokens) out of source code.
Use environment variables or configuration files instead of hardcoding secrets.
	•	

When adding authentication/authorization, use JWT or HMAC-based schemes consistent with existing code.
	•	id: cloakcat-scope-control
patterns:
	•	“**/*.rs”
rules:
	•	

When the user asks for a change, only modify the minimum number of files needed.
Do not rewrite or restructure unrelated parts of the project.
	•	

Prefer to extend existing patterns (structs, modules, error types) instead of inventing new ones without reason.
	•	

If a requested change seems too large, propose a small, incremental step and implement that step.

- id: cat-server-specific
patterns:
	•	“cat-server/**/*.rs”
rules:
	•	

For HTTP handlers, follow existing Axum patterns in this project.
Use typed request/response structs and return proper status codes.
	•	

When adding database queries, use sqlx macros and existing PgPool pattern.
Handle database errors gracefully and avoid panics.
	•	id: cat-agent-specific
patterns:
	•	“cat-agent/**/*.rs”
rules:
	•	

The agent must stay simple and stable.
Avoid heavy dependencies and keep the runtime footprint small.
	•	

Do not introduce blocking I/O in async contexts.
Use tokio async APIs consistently.
